{
  "version": "1.3",
  "description": "Elocin core deterministic tagging lexicon v1. Universal pre-K-2 vocabulary. Method keys are a CLOSED set of 16; curriculum packs add triggers to these keys but never new keys. Skill keys are additive over the pre-lexicon set (existing keys kept stable). Per-trigger tiers: triggers_high = exact hit auto-applies; triggers_medium (single common nouns / ambiguous) = suggestion only, never auto-applied. Normalization preserves ':' and '-' so 1:1 / 1-on-1 match. Negation and outcome word lists are DISJOINT (no double-counting).",
